{"cursor":"28487","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n{{Infobox document |document_name = Charter of Fundamental Rights of the\nEuropean Union |image = 01CFREU-Preamble-crop.jpg |image_width = 250px\n|image_caption = The preamble of the Charter |date_created = 2 October 2000\n|date_ratified = 7 December 2000 |location_of_document = |writer = European\nConvention |signers = Institutions and member states of the European Union\n|purpose = Consolidate and enshrine the broad array of rights afforded to\ncitizens of the European Union |wikisource = Charter of Fundamental Rights of\nthe European Union }} The 'Charter of Fundamental Rights of the European Union'\nenshrines certain political, social, and economic rights for European Union (EU)\ncitizens and residents into EU law. It was drafted by the European Convention\nand solemnly proclaimed on 7 December 2000 by the European Parliament, the\nCouncil of Ministers and the European Commission. However its then legal status\nwas uncertain and it did not have full legal effect until the entry into force of the Treaty of Lisbon on 1\nDecember 2009.\n\nUnder the Charter, the European Union (EU) must act and legislate consistently\nwith the Charter and the EU's courts will strike down EU legislation which\ncontravenes it. The Charter applies to the EU's institutions, and the its EU\nmember states but only when the latter are implementing EU law. The Charter does\nnot extend the competences of the EU.\n","linknr":547,"url":"Charter_of_Fundamental_Rights_of_the_European_Union","recorded":1364040389,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Charter_of_Fundamental_Rights_of_the_European_Union&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Charter_of_Fundamental_Rights_of_the_European_Union&action=edit","//en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChange